; W3C "A Well-Known URL for Changing Passwords"
; https://www.w3.org/TR/change-password-url/
;
; Browser password managers (Chrome, Safari, 1Password, Bitwarden) check
; this URL to surface a "change password" deep link to users when their
; saved credentials are compromised. The expected behavior is a 303 to
; the actual change-password page.
;
; This file is deliberately minimal — Cloudflare Pages will serve it as
; a 200 (instead of the spec-recommended 302). Browser password managers
; tolerate either response so long as the URL exists. The actual
; redirect happens via `_redirects` (see frontend/_redirects).
